cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CC 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to predict notional anaphora in English. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses an ensemble approach to prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses the OntoNotes corpus, which is a large dataset, and the results suggest that global factors such as genre have a strong effect on the choice of referring expression, indicating the use of statistical methods (cs.LG). The paper also deals with coreference resolution, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with linguistic phenomena, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CC).
